The paper proposes a new deep probabilistic model for learning a disentangled representation of a set of grouped observations, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on learning a representation that reflects the semantics behind a specific grouping of the data suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of face images as an example also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.NE) or computational linguistics (cs.CL), which often deal with similar types of data.
